parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Shifter Failure due to Snow/Slush Ingress
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission shifter can cause the vehicle to become stuck in gear, making it difficult or impossible to shift, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Unable to shift transmission from D to another position like R
P
N
vehicle can only drive forward
unable to turn off the engine or restart the vehicle in gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The throttle body sticking wide open can cause the vehicle to accelerate uncontrollably, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Throttle body gets stuck wide open after the engine reaches operating temperature
warning signs include on-off throttle use
no error codes displayed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal Softness and Transmission Gear Confusion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The soft brake pedal can lead to extended stopping distances, increasing the risk of accidents, while the transmission's inability to select the correct gear can cause loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft
requires both feet on the brake pedal to stop
transmission has difficulty selecting the correct gear
resulting in poor fuel economy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the DEF heater can cause the vehicle to operate at reduced speeds, increasing the risk of accidents, and can lead to engine damage.
symptoms: DEF light and check engine light illuminated on the dashboard
error code "P20C1 Reductant Heater C Control Circuit/OPEN" displayed
vehicle speed limited to 55MPH or lower.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure with Soft Pedal and Loss of Stopping Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the brakes can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down, leaving the driver with no control over the vehicle.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down
the vehicle rolls backwards or moves unexpectedly
the brake pedal must be pumped to get the vehicle to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking brake system can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries, especially when the brakes fail simultaneously.
symptoms: The parking brake warning message appears on the dashboard
the parking brake does not engage
the vehicle rolls or moves unexpectedly when the brakes fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose traction and stability, leading to accidents or injuries, especially when the brakes fail simultaneously.
symptoms: The myGMC app notifies the driver of the need to service the ABS system
the vehicle exhibits unusual vibrations or noises when driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden separation and blowout of a tire can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. Additionally, the damage to the vehicle's body and potential for subsequent tire failures can result in costly repairs and downtime.
symptoms: Sudden and unexpected tire blowout
loss of vehicle control
difficulty steering
tire separation
damage to vehicle body and surrounding components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden opening of the tailgate while driving can cause cargo to shift or fall out, obstructing the road and potentially causing accidents or injuries to other drivers or pedestrians.
symptoms: The tailgate opens unexpectedly while driving
the tailgate does not stay closed
the tailgate latch feels loose or weak
the tailgate makes a rattling or clunking noise while driving.
